.TH LIME-LSP 1 "May 2026" "Lime 0.5.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lime-lsp \- Language Server Protocol server for Lime grammar files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lime-lsp
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lime-lsp
is a Language Server Protocol (LSP) server for
.B .lime
grammar files.
It speaks LSP 3.17 (subset) over standard input/output framed with
HTTP-style
.B Content-Length
headers.
The server is a separate binary from the
.BR lime (1)
parser generator: for live diagnostics it
.BR fork (2)/ exec (3)s
.B lime -L
on a temporary copy of the open document; for navigation features
(go-to-definition, hover, document outline) it runs an
in-process tokenizer.
.PP
.B lime-lsp
takes no positional arguments and reads / writes JSON-RPC 2.0
on stdio only.
There is no daemon mode and no socket transport; editor
integrations spawn the server as a child process per workspace.
.PP
v0.5.0 ships LSP "Phase 1": single-document scope, full-text
sync, diagnostics, definition, hover, document symbol.  See
.B docs/LSP.md
for the implementation guide and
.B editors/lime-lsp-config.md
for editor wire-up recipes (eglot, lsp-mode, Neovim
.BR lspconfig ,
VS Code).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-lime " path"
Path to the
.BR lime (1)
binary used for diagnostics.
Overrides
.B $LIME_BIN
and the
.B PATH
search.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print the LSP server version (matches
.BR LIME_VERSION_STRING )
and exit.
.SH "ADVERTISED CAPABILITIES"
The
.B ServerCapabilities
object returned at
.B initialize
time is the authoritative list of supported features:
.PP
.RS
.EX
{
  "textDocumentSync": { "openClose": true, "change": 1, "save": true },
  "definitionProvider":     true,
  "hoverProvider":          true,
  "documentSymbolProvider": true
}
.EE
.RE
.PP
.B "change: 1"
is
.B TextDocumentSyncKind.Full
-- the client sends the full buffer text on every
.BR didChange ;
incremental sync is deferred.
.PP
Per-method status:
.TP
.B initialize / initialized / shutdown / exit
Standard lifecycle.  The server returns
.B serverInfo.version
populated from
.BR LIME_VERSION_STRING .
.TP
.B textDocument/didOpen, didChange, didSave, didClose
Maintain the per-document buffer state and push diagnostics on
each event;
.B didClose
publishes an empty diagnostic array to clear stale markers.
.TP
.B textDocument/publishDiagnostics
Server-to-client notification.
For each open document, parsed
.B lime -L
output (lint and parser-stage messages) becomes an LSP
.BR Diagnostic ;
severity maps:
.B error
\(rA 1,
.B warning
\(rA 2,
.B note / info
\(rA 3,
.B hint
\(rA 4.
.TP
.B textDocument/definition
Jump from a non-terminal RHS reference to its LHS-defining rule,
or from a terminal use to the
.B %token
declaration site.
.TP
.B textDocument/hover
Return either a one-line directive description (covering
.BR %name ,
.BR %token ,
.BR %type ,
.BR %extra_argument ,
.BR %extends ,
.BR %dialect ,
.BR %embed ,
.BR %locations ,
and the rest of the directive surface), or a symbol summary
(kind, declaring line, usage count).
.TP
.B textDocument/documentSymbol
Flat outline of every directive, terminal, and non-terminal in
the document, in declaration order with kinds
.B Key
(directive),
.B Constant
(terminal),
.B Function
(non-terminal).
.PP
The following methods are advertised as
.B unsupported
and are intentionally deferred:
.B textDocument/completion ,
.B textDocument/references ,
.B textDocument/rename ,
.B textDocument/semanticTokens/full ,
.B textDocument/codeAction ,
.B workspace/symbol .
The first three need a persistent cross-document grammar
model;
.B codeAction
pairs with the linter's auto-fix surface, which has not yet
been wired.
.SH "ENVIRONMENT"
.TP
.B LIME_BIN
Path to the
.B lime
binary used for diagnostics.
Searched in this order:
.B \-\-lime
argument,
.BR LIME_BIN ,
literal
.B lime
on
.BR PATH .
.TP
.B TMPDIR
Used for the temporary file that holds the open document while
.B lime -L
runs against it.
Falls back to
.B /tmp
when unset.
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.TP
.B 0
Clean shutdown via the LSP
.B shutdown
\(rA
.B exit
sequence.
.TP
.B 1
LSP protocol violation, malformed JSON-RPC frame, or fatal I/O
error on stdio.
.TP
.B 2
Argument-parsing failure.
.SH "PROCESS MODEL"
.RS
.EX
editor  <-- JSON-RPC 2.0 over stdio -->  lime-lsp
                                            |
                                            +--> fork+exec  lime -L /tmp/<doc>.lime
                                            |    (per didOpen / didChange /
                                            |     didSave; output piped back
                                            |     and parsed line-by-line)
                                            |
                                            +--> in-process tokenizer
                                                 (definition, hover,
                                                  documentSymbol; ~250 LOC)
.EE
.RE
.PP
The LSP target is intentionally decoupled from the Lime parser
runtime: it does
.I not
link
.B lime_parser_lib
and does
.I not
include any header that would force a recompile when the
parser internals change.  Every byte the LSP ships lives in
.BR src/lsp/ .
.SH "WIRE FORMAT"
JSON-RPC 2.0 framed with HTTP-style headers:
.PP
.RS
.EX
Content-Length: <N>\\r\\n
\\r\\n
<N bytes of UTF-8 JSON>
.EE
.RE
.PP
The bundled JSON parser (\fBsrc/lsp/lsp_json.[ch]\fP) is
hand-rolled in ~600 lines and handles UTF-16 surrogate pairs
in
.B \\uXXXX
escapes; no external JSON dependency is linked.
.SH "LIMITATIONS"
.IP \(bu 2
Single document at a time.  Definition / hover / outline do
not cross
.B %extends
or
.B %import
file boundaries.
.IP \(bu 2
Full-text sync only (no incremental).
.IP \(bu 2
No completion, references, rename, semantic tokens, or code
actions.
.IP \(bu 2
POSIX-only.  The diagnostics path requires
.BR fork (2),
.BR execvp (3),
and
.BR pipe (2).
On Windows, run the server inside WSL.  A native Win32
implementation is future work.
